  "title": "Assistant Manager, People & Culture",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Support the understanding and application of the Group Talent Framework, Talent Marketplace structure, and its integration with Individual Development Plans (IDPs). <br /></li><li>Assist in preparing Talent Marketplace usage analytics and reports and propose improvement ideas based on insights.</li></ul><ul><li><p>Support basic Performance Enablement Process (PEP) activities, including understanding talent processes and MSPS requirements.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Assist in tracking the annual P&C calendar and support BP transactional activities.</p></li><li><p>Support annual P&C activity planning and coordination.</p></li><li><p>Gain exposure to budgeting processes, including cost allocation principles and contract arrangements.</p></li><li><p>Assist in managing P&C projects, including basic schedule, risk, and issue tracking.</p></li></ul><p><ul><li>Support initiatives aimed at embedding a performance-driven culture that fosters innovation.<br /></li><li>Assist with initiatives aligned to GHQ expectations, Employee Engagement Survey (EES) insights, and DEI/Inclusion principles</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Business Administration, HRM</li><li>More than 6 years of relevant working experience </li><li>Possess strong technical acumen, including Excel, PowerPoint and P&CIS (SAP SuccessFactors and ServiceNow experience a plus)</li><li>Excellent written and spoken language skills with an ability to understand employee queries and interact with different stakeholder in P&C and business</li><li>Knowledge of fundamental P&C practices including employee data, talent, learning, performance, recruitment and compensation</li><li>Strong organizational, time management skills     </li><li>Able to meet deadlines and work effectively under pressure</li><li>Eye for details, creative, team player and self-motivated </li><li>Possess good interpersonal and communication skills and able to work with people at all levels</li></ul>",
